# Band 8 Sample Answer

## Introduction

The three line graphs compare five countries in terms of the number of hospital beds per 1,000 people and the percentages of patients waiting either up to 30 days or more than 30 days for elective surgery in 2010, 2014 and 2018.

**翻译：**
这三张折线图比较了五个国家在2010年、2014年和2018年的每千人医院床位数量，以及等待择期手术不超过30天和超过30天的患者比例。

---

## Overview

Overall, Canada and Australia had the highest numbers of hospital beds at the beginning of the period, although both figures declined over time. Sweden showed the opposite trend, with bed availability increasing steadily. In terms of surgery waiting times, Sweden consistently recorded the highest proportion of patients treated within 30 days, while the UK and Canada experienced rising percentages of patients waiting longer than one month.

**翻译：**
总体来看，加拿大和澳大利亚在期初拥有最多的医院床位，但两国的数据随后均有所下降。相反，瑞典的床位数量稳步增长。在手术等待时间方面，瑞典始终拥有最高比例的30天内接受手术的患者，而英国和加拿大等待超过一个月的患者比例则有所上升。

---

## Body Paragraph 1

Regarding hospital beds, Canada started at approximately 5 beds per 1,000 people in 2010, before declining gradually to around 4 by 2018. Australia followed a similar downward trend, falling from roughly 4.5 to just below 4. By contrast, Sweden increased steadily from about 3.8 beds to 4.5 over the same period. The UK saw the sharpest fall, dropping from just above 4 to under 3 beds per 1,000 people, while Mexico remained comparatively low despite a slight increase.

**翻译：**
在医院床位方面，加拿大在2010年约为每千人5张床位，随后逐渐下降至2018年的约4张。澳大利亚也呈现类似的下降趋势，从约4.5下降到略低于4。相比之下，瑞典则稳步增长，从约3.8上升至4.5。英国出现了最明显的下降，其数据从略高于4降至不足3张床位，而墨西哥虽然略有增长，但整体水平依然较低。

---

## Body Paragraph 2

As for waiting times, Sweden performed best throughout the period, with the proportion of patients treated within 30 days rising from approximately 68% in 2010 to over 80% in 2018. Australia also experienced moderate improvement. In contrast, the figures for the UK and Canada declined noticeably, reaching only about 40% by the end of the period. This pattern was reflected in the percentage of patients waiting more than 30 days, where the UK and Canada rose sharply to around 60%, whereas Sweden reduced its figure significantly from about 33% to below 20%.

**翻译：**
至于等待时间，瑞典在整个时期内表现最佳，其30天内接受手术的患者比例从2010年的约68%上升至2018年的80%以上。澳大利亚的数据也有所改善。相比之下，英国和加拿大的数据明显下降，到期末仅约为40%。这一趋势同样反映在等待超过30天的患者比例中：英国和加拿大的数据大幅上升至约60%，而瑞典则显著下降，从约33%降至不足20%。

